  <front>
   <head>SONNET [08] VIII. To Spring.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">AGAIN the wood, and long withdrawing vale,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In many a tint of tender green are drest,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where the young leaves unfolding, scarce conceal,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Beneath their early shade, the half form'd nest</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Of finch or woodlark; and the primrose pale,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And lavish cowslip, wildly scatter'd round,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Give their sweet spirits to the sighing gale.</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ah, season of delight! — could aught be found</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To soothe awhile the tortur'd bosom's pain,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Of Sorrow's rankling shaft to cure the wound,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And bring life's first delusions once again,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">'Twere surely met in thee! — thy prospect fair,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thy sounds of harmony, thy balmy air,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Have power to cure all sadness — but despair.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
